HEADWORD: Buffle-headed
<hw>Buf"fle-head`ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having a large head, like a
buffalo; dull; stupid; blundering.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>So fell this <qex>buffle-headed</qex> giant.</q>
<rj><qau>Gayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>buffo</ent>⟦br⟧
